&lt;p&gt;# Comments: 0&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=49024809</guid><pubDate>Thu, 23 Jul 2026 17:01:24 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Are we in the era of AI slop landing pages?</title><link>https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=49024805</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Sorry for making it sound like a rant, but is anyone else actually tired of seeing the same AI slop landing pages? Those same card layouts and color shcemes? And those fake metrics, "Trusted by 10,000+ professionals", no bro my SimilarWeb extension shows 0 traffic on your site for the past 3 months..&lt;p&gt;I mean yeah I get it that you need to ship fast but maybe like delay your launch for 12-24 hrs and make at least a half decent and appealing landing page. These landing pages remind me of that scene from Toy Story where there was a shelf full of Buzz lightyear figurines. Do people actually have 0 taste?&lt;p&gt;Do you guys trust such apps especially in B2B space? With a landing page that screams 0% trust and 100% AI generated, you bet I'm not gonna give you access to my credentials or repos etc..&lt;p&gt;Your landing page is the first impression of your app, at least make it count..&lt;p&gt;This concludes my rant  Anyone else feels the same?&lt;/p&gt;
